<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="880" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d880">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/1–245: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-02">January 2,
                                        1945</date>.<lb/>[Received January 2—8:49 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>6. Moscow papers January 2 announce delegation of Provisional
                                Hungarian Government has arrived in Moscow for armistice
                                negotiations. It consists of János Gyondesy [<hi rend="italic">Gyöngyösy</hi>] Minister of Foreign Affairs and President of
                                Delegation; Colonel General János Vörös; and Istvan Balog, Secretary
                                of State.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Caserta as 1.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>